Ambiguous – having more than one meaning
Example: His answer was ambiguous.
Brisk – quick and energetic
Example: She took a brisk walk in the morning.
Conceal – to hide something
Example: He tried to conceal his feelings.
Deteriorate – to become worse
Example: The building began to deteriorate.
Empathy – understanding others’ feelings
Example: A good leader shows empathy.
Frugal – careful with money
Example: He is very frugal with his spending.
Gratify – to please or satisfy
Example: It gratified her to see success.
Hostile – unfriendly or aggressive
Example: The crowd became hostile.
Illuminate – to light up or explain
Example: The teacher illuminated the topic well.
Jubilant – extremely happy
Example: They were jubilant after winning.
